Fix: prevent premature Swiss round generation

Bug: When manually inputting 1 R1 match, system immediately generated
R2 (and even potentially finalized Swiss). Same issue for group stage.

Cause: _generate_swiss_next_round computed active teams from records and
generated next round whenever active > 0, regardless of whether the
current round was fully complete.

Fix: _is_current_round_complete() checks if all matches in current round
are completed. _generate_swiss_next_round now:
  - Returns False early if current round is not fully complete
  - progress_tournament returns 'waiting' action when R1 partial
  - Returns 'swiss_done' only when current round is complete AND no new
    round is generated

Same fix applied to _resolve_group_placeholder_matches via
_is_groups_complete() check in progress_tournament.

Tested:
  - Major manual flow: R1 done 1/4 -> waiting, 2/4 -> waiting, 3/4 -> waiting, 4/4 -> swiss_next
  - R2 same pattern
  - R3 finalizes after both matches done
  - Rankings correct: 4 advance, 4 eliminated with #9-12
  - Sim All still works for all 3 tournament types
